  "reasoning": "Now let me check when the next FOMC meeting is and look at Fed funds futures to understand market expectations.The next FOMC meeting is March 17-18, 2026 — well after the Feb 26 resolution date. So no rate change is expected before resolution. Let me now compute the distribution analytically.**SOFR on Feb 26, 2026 Forecast:**\n\nThe forecast is tightly centered around **3.65%**, reflecting SOFR's remarkable stability under the current Fed regime:\n\n- **No rate change coming**: The next FOMC meeting is March 17-18, well after the Feb 26 resolution date. The target range stays at 3.50-3.75%.\n- **Empirical stability**: Since the December 2025 rate cut, SOFR has traded in a 3.63-3.69 range on normal (non-month-end) days, with 77% of observations at 3.64-3.66.\n- **Calendar effects minimal**: Feb 26 is a Thursday, the second-to-last business day of February. Historical data shows negligible month-end pressure at this position (Jan 29, same relative position, was 3.65).\n\n| Percentile | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| 10th | 3.63 |\n| 20th | 3.64 |\n| 40th | 3.65 |\n| 60th | 3.66 |\n| 80th | 3.67 |\n| 90th | 3.69 |\n\nThe distribution is intentionally very tight — this reflects the empirical reality that SOFR barely moves between FOMC meetings absent repo market stress events.",
